    "Carbon scaffolds were identified by the carbon framework of a molecule, wherein all nonhydrogen atoms were transformed into carbon atoms and all bonds were replaced by single bonds (illustrated in Fig.",
    "The scaffold novelty score was formulated by incorporating both atom and carbon scaffold scores.",
    "Each of these scores determined whether the corresponding scaffold was present in any molecule within the training set, as determined by Equations ((9)-(11)).",
    "Both structural and scaffold novelty contribute to the overall novelty score, i.e., Equation (12), ranging from 0 (for molecules very close to molecules the training set) to 1.2 (for molecules with no ECFP overlap with the training set and no shared scaffolds).",
